      "avalancheActivity": {
        "comment": "In some regions up to 40 cm of snow, and even more in some localities, has fallen. The wind was moderate to strong. The wind slabs of the last few days represent the main danger. They must be evaluated with care and prudence in all aspects. The avalanche prone locations are to be found in particular at the base of rock walls, and adjacent to ridgelines and in gullies and bowls. As the day progresses the likelihood of moist avalanches being released will increase gradually. Avalanches can in many places be released, even by a single winter sport participant. <br/> Backcountry touring calls for experience in the assessment of avalanche danger and careful route selection.",
        "highlights": "At elevated altitudes a considerable avalanche danger will prevail."
